snippet.title: Best tech cars
snippet.description: The following cars represent the most technically advanced available.

snippet.title: 2012 Chrysler 300 SRT8
snippet.description: Although a bit archaic in its power-train hardware, the 2012 Chrysler 300 SRT8 features modern cabin electronics and full-size sedan comfort.

snippet.title: iPad (fall 2012)
snippet.description: The latest iPad adds several tweaks and improvements to secure its position at the top of the tablet heap. It's better all around, but third-gen owners need not apply.

snippet.title: Amazon Kindle Fire (2012)
snippet.description: The Kindle Fire (2012) takes it up a notch in value, but is tethered to the same design oversights of the original.

snippet.title: 2012 Mercedes-Benz CLS550
snippet.description: Mercedes-Benz bolsters its reputation for luxury with the 2012 CLS550. A powerful and efficient engine propels this sleek ride, and there are a number of advanced driver-assistance features.

snippet.title: Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1 (2012)
snippet.description: The Samsung Galaxy Note 10.1 is the best Samsung tablet yet. If you can get over its somewhat high price, it's a sound Android tablet investment.

snippet.title: 2012 Toyota RAV4 EV
snippet.description: The fact that the 2012 Toyota RAV4 EV is an electric SUV is less compelling than its range, where it comes in a little stronger than most electric cars.

snippet.title: Amazon Kindle (2012)
snippet.description: The $69 Amazon Kindle is an excellent no-frills e-book reader for anyone whoâ€™s willing to forgo a built-in light or a touch screen.

snippet.title: Apple iPod Shuffle (2012)
snippet.description: The Apple iPod Shuffle is an adorable way to take your favorite songs on the go, but sometimes it's too small for its own good.
